author: Simon Coates
description: From Doris Salcedo’s 'Shibboleth' to Kara Walker’s anti-imperial fountain, the commissions have frequently challenged viewers to reckon with global history.
title: Looking Back at 25 Years of Tate Turbine Hall Commissions

author: Mark Minevich
description: Mark Minevich, a globally recognized A.I. strategist and advisor to Fortune 500s and world governments, unpacks new research revealing how woefully unprepared Gen Z in America’s heartland is for the A.I.-driven economy. While urban centers and elite institutions race ahead, students and workers in rural and lower-income regions are being left behind—with no clear policies, no practical training and no time to waste.
title: The Coming A.I. Catastrophe for Middle America’s Gen Z
